# Code owners — GitHub requests a review from the owner(s) when a PR touches a matching
# path, and (with a branch ruleset that enables "Require review from Code Owners") makes
# that review a merge gate. This is the governance half of software assurance: nothing
# security-sensitive merges without the right eyes on it.
#
# Owners are auto-requested for review. Swap @fgarofalo56 for a team handle
# (e.g. @your-org/maintainers) if this repo gains multiple maintainers.

# Default owner for everything not matched below.
*                       @fgarofalo56

# --- Security-sensitive surfaces (always reviewed by an owner) ---
/.github/                @fgarofalo56
/.github/workflows/      @fgarofalo56
SECURITY.md              @fgarofalo56
/docs/SECURITY.md        @fgarofalo56
/docs/SOFTWARE-ASSURANCE.md  @fgarofalo56

# Identity, gateway, and data-classification config gate access to data.
/services/identity/      @fgarofalo56
/services/gateway/       @fgarofalo56
/data/classification.yml @fgarofalo56

# Infrastructure-as-code and deploy scripts.
/infra/                  @fgarofalo56
/scripts/                @fgarofalo56
